ROOT CAUSE ANALYSIS REPORT — HEAVY GAS COMPRESSOR H4
Incident Ref: IR-2024-124 | Report ID: RCA-002 | Asset: Heavy Gas Compressor H4

1. SYMPTOMS & CAUSES
- Symptoms: Gas pressure drop across Stage 2 cylinder, high crankcase oil consumption.
- Root Cause: Piston ring seal degradation resulting from thermal overload during extended continuous peak-load operation.
- Corrective Actions: Replace complete seal kit, re-calibrate pressure sensor, convert action to Work Order WO-105.
- Cross-Record Insight Note: Inspection INSP-003 on COMPRESSOR_H4 was 15 days overdue prior to this incident.